{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a 6-month time limit for police misconduct investigations",
        "additional_details": "The law should also require:\r\n\r\n* A formal review at 3 months\r\n* Welfare and occupational health support for officers under investigation\r\n* Publication of anonymised data on investigation times and outcomes\r\n\r\nProlonged investigations can undermine fairness, efficiency, and workforce wellbeing. Clear time limits with independent oversight would support timely, proportionate decision-making while maintaining public confidence in police accountability.",
        "background": "We ask the Government to legislate for a statutory 6-month time limit for completing police misconduct investigations.\r\n\r\nWhere cases cannot reasonably be concluded within 6 months, extensions should require approval from an independent authority, with clear justification and regular review.",
